data.name: richTextBoxIO.Text
data.value:
List of commands: C : Creates a new text file O : Opens an existing text file R : Reads a text file that has been opened S : Sorts a text file alphabetically and displays the alphabetized version W : Writes to a text file that has been opened ? : Brings up this list of commands
Other useful information: Write will automatically append the current textfile. If you want to overwrite a textfile use the C command to create a new text file and use the same name. It will overwrite the file and create a blank text file with the same name.
When you open or create a file the previous file is closed.
